  "headline": "Content Security Policy (CSP)",
  "description": "Content Security Policy (CSP) is a security standard that helps prevent XSS, clickjacking, and code injection attacks by controlling which resources a web page is allowed to load. It is delivered via HTTP headers (`Content-Security-Policy`) or `<meta>` tags.",
